  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Conflict-Affected Populations in the Far North of Cameroon through Providing Humanitarian Actors with Reliable and Timely Displacement Figures and Trends</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to support crisis affected populations in Cameroon and to address their most urgent needs, IOM seeks to continue providing the humanitarian community in Far North with information on displacement trends and most pressing sectoral needs of conflict-affected populations, through multi-sector needs assessments and mobility tracking rounds, while also producing and disseminating regular information on the sudden forced displacements and urgent needs of displaced populations to inform the humanitarian community including the Far North Rapid Response Mechanism. Finally, to strengthen local capacities with an ultimate goal to transfer the responsibility to Cameroon actors for multi-sector needs assessments, IOM is building the capacities for local non-governmental organisations partners to increasingly collect accurate and triangulated data on the humanitarian needs of displaced populations.</narrative>
  </description>
